The paper discusses constraint programming and its application to permutation and injection problems. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC). However, given the focus on constraint programming, cs.AI and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.DM, and cs.CC.
